    <a href="/reading/finance-1/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to finance</a>

    <h1>Risk Management</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">OpenStax Principles of Finance (<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC BY 4.0</a>) &middot; <a href="https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/15-401-finance-theory-i-fall-2008/">MIT OCW 15.401</a> (<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</a>)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Risk management does not eliminate risk &mdash; it transforms risk you cannot bear into risk you can. The core tools are <strong>hedging</strong>, <strong>diversification</strong>, and <strong>insurance</strong>. Value at Risk (VaR) measures how bad things could get.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Risk types diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 200" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
